## 7. Adding capability modules post-install (manual)

Modules live under `.claude/skills/<module-name>/`. Each module is a directory with a `SKILL.md` describing what it does and how the agent invokes it.

To add a module after the initial install:

```bash
# from inside the agent-scaffolder repo:
cp -r <agent-scaffolder>/skills/<module-name> <this-vault>/.claude/skills/
```

Restart the agent (`./restart.sh`) and it picks up the new skill.

Available V1 modules: inbox-triage, calendar, scheduling, follow-up-tracking, meeting-prep, comms-drafts, light-research, google-workspace, google-workspace-mcp, zapier-webhook.
Planned V1.1: travel, expenses, send-on-behalf comms.

